message:
@Chris_Huntley, I've always assumed that the world at the end of a story (specifically a Good/Success story) looked like the theme browser -- all at rest -- while any other outcome was still out of whack. 

And, that Failure/Bad stories were more out of whack. (Is there some measure of degree? Can things be more or less messed up?)

I'm not sure it has a practical application to how I work, but is my assumption right?
